rComments: I personally loved his classes and the way he teaches them, but his tests (and quizzes) are very difficult and include subjects not touched much like biochem. Learn everything, understand 100%, and study every week. I'm not sure if that was the case before the pandemic, but I found the final particularly difficult for a first year course.

Im very surprised with the comments posted for this professor. Hes extremely disorganized and often posts lectures late. This makes it difficult for students with a heavy course load to plan adequately. The questions on his quizzes are also difficult or ambiguous and he often tests on material that has not been studied. Not very impressed.

très bon prof, il explique bien la matiere et a un bon sens de l'humour, par contre lors de ses examens il est important de bien comprendre et maitriser la matiere et ce il faut aussi bien l'expliquer. je vous suggere de vous pratiquez à l'expliquer a qqun d'autre dans le cours ou encore mieux un de vos pairs qui ne connait pas la matiere :)

Nicolas est un professeur extrêmement passionné de sa matière. Il s'exprime d'une façon très professionnel et il explique très bien la matière. Il a un bon sens d'humour et il est très interessant. J'ai hâte d'aller à ses cours, même s'ils sont à 8h30 du matin !

Great lecturer - makes his subject matter really interesting! Which is really appreciated when you have class at 8:30 AM! He uses real world examples to help us relate to what we're studying. It's not an easy class - you should attend every class and ask him if there's something you don't understand. He makes himself very accessible to students.

He is such a good prof. His lectures are so interesting and he is very knowledgable on the topics as he has had lots of experience. He was always very patient with answering questions and giving feedback. I think all his assessments were very fair and he was clear with expectations. I am looking forward to having him again next semester!
